%h3
  Basics
%p
  %ul
    %li
      The system used on this website is 
      =(link_to "Jyutping", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jyutping") + "."
      There is also 
      =link_to "yale", "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yale_Romanization"
      and others.
    %li
      There are 6 tones in Jyutping (technically 9, but we'll ignore that). This mnemonic device passes through all 6 major tones with very common and distinct words.
    %li
      Below translates into 
      =surround '"' do
        %b 1 small bowl of beef brisket noodles

%h3
  The Tones

.the-tones
  %table.table
    %thead
      %tr
        %th
          Tone #
        %th
          Character
        %th
          Jyutping
        %th
          English Meaning
    -@the_tones.to_enum.with_index(1) do |tone_ex, index|
      %tr
        %td
          =(index.to_s) + "."
        %td
          =link_to tone_ex[:chars_trad], tone_ex[:link]
        %td
          %a.sm2_button{:href => "http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-can/sound/#{tone_ex[:jyutping]}.wav"}
          =tone_ex[:jyutping]
        %td
          =tone_ex[:english]

